Gussy,

I wish you luck in getting them for that price.

Once you get dinoz w/ the right gathering skills, the energy only shows up 1 per grid. That means - on average - it takes 36 turns to earn one energy.

Even with Merchant skill, it takes 810 * 36 = 29,160 to get one. Or, the patient way of over 1 month.

If you wish to buy energy, then you will be paying for the convenience and speed.

On december 29, 2009
Piemaster
That's a very narrow view of cost. The total 'cost' of supplying a Kabuki or Kabuki Egg to the market are:

1. The cost of all the ingredients, either bought on the market or the opportunity cost of levelling up your dinos as collectors rather than fighters or a mix of both.

2. The inconvenience of chasing Yakuzi all over the map (plus the 10k you have to pay him of course).

3. The turns and food that your dinos used on the various fights to complete the Kabuki quest, including the wasted turns resting before and/or after the fights.

4. One of your three Kabukis that can't ever be replaced unless you buy one back from the market yourself.

5. If you take the long view, all the turns, irmas and/or money that you used to get your dinos to the point where they can complete the Yakuzi quest in the first place.


So I'm not sure how you're really arriving at this 100 cost, but I'm sure it's wildly inaccurate. And given the number of people seemingly willing to pay 300+ on the market for a Kabuki or an egg, I think I am not alone in that opinion.
